articles.author: Rod Mcguirk, Associated Press
articles.title: Skydiver dangles at 15,000 feet after parachute catches on plane's tail in Australia - KSL.com
articles.description: Australian accident investigators have released dramatic images showing a skydiver's parachute entangled on an airplane's tail, leaving him dangling at 15,000 feet.
articles.content:
MELBOURNE, Australia Australian accident investigators on Thursday released dramatic images of a skydiver's parachute becoming entangled on an airplane's tail, leaving him dangling at 15,000 feet.
